2 of sugarcane liquid.
3 (c) Dewatered pulp derived from bagasse; recognized by the United
4 States Environmental Protection Agency as a fuel pursuant to 40 CFR 241.4.
5 (19) "Traditional farm practices" means those accepted and customary
6 standards established by similar agricultural operations under similar circumstances
7 using established best management practices. Best management practices for animal
8 feeding operations and confined animal feeding operations shall be determined by
9 the Louisiana Department of Agriculture and Forestry in conjunction with the LSU
10 AgCenter.
11 * * *
12 §3607. Local ordinances
13 * * *
14 E. No parish or municipal governing authority may enact or enforce any
15 ordinance prohibiting the storage of sugarcane bagasse biomass when it is
16 stored in accordance with a best management practice plan that has been
17 approved by the Department of Agriculture and Forestry in writing and
18 provided to the Department of Environmental Quality.
19 Section 2. This Act shall become effective upon signature by the governor or, if not
